  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Miramare &amp; Spa is right in front of the stunning Bay of Silence, which has one of the best beaches in <a data-udi="umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb}" title="Liguria">Liguria</a>. It’s been awarded Blue Flag status so you can expect high environmental standards. It’s sandy with a gentle slope into the sea, which is lovely and clear.</p>
<h2>Private beach club and spa</h2>
<p>The Miramare has a private beach club (payable locally) so you can spend all day there relaxing if you like. Speaking of relaxing, check out the hotel's Karma Spa and treat yourself to a massage or beauty treatment (payable locally). </p>
<h2>Seafront Location</h2>
<p>The hotel makes the most of its seafront location with large glass windows in the lounge and wine bar so you can grab a drink, sit back and enjoy the view. The rooms have modern décor with views of the old town or courtyard. If you like falling asleep to the sound of the sea every night, upgrade to a Superior Room. The balcony looks out over the beach and the views are incredible.</p>
<h2>Delicious food on the beach</h2>
<p>The hotel’s à la carte restaurant is something special. You can upgrade your half board meals to the Restaurant Baia del Silenzio which appears in the Michelin guide thanks to its gourmet food and fab location right on the beach. There are even tables set up on the sand. You’ve got plenty more choices of places to eat in Sestri Levante– everything’s within walking distance thanks to the hotel’s central location.</p>]]></description>
