  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Double Rooms </strong>are around 19-24m² and sleep two people, plus a child aged 1 - 3 years. They have views of the old town or courtyard.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Rooms</strong> are around 32m² and sleep up to three people. They have views of the old town or courtyard.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Sea View Rooms</strong> are around 19m² and sleep up to two people. They look out directly over the Bay of Silence so you can enjoy sea views from your private balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Junior Suites</strong> are around 34m² and sleep up to two people. They have king-size beds, private balcony with sea views, a seating area, bathrobe, slippers and whirlpool.</p>
<p><strong>Sea View Suites</strong> are are elegant and spacious at around 46m² and sleep two people, plus a child aged 1-3 years. They have a comfortable separate lounge area, two bathrooms and a whirlpool. The doors open up to a French balcony overlooking the Bay of Silence. Family suites are also available.</p>
<p><strong>Family Suites</strong> are spacious and sleep up to four people, ideal for keeping the family in one place.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Air-conditioning</li>
<li>Shower</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Safe</li>
</ul>
<p>Cots are available on request.</p>
<p><strong>Local fees &amp; taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. €2 per person per night (aged 12+) for a maximum of 7 nights is payable locally.</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
